Deputy President David Mabuza says government has no intention to privatise Eskom. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Deputy President David Mabuza says government has no intention to privatise Eskom. He reiterated that plans to split the power utility into three divisions are not aimed at selling it off. READ: Mabuza: Eskom must be supported Mabuza was answering questions in the National Council of Provinces. "Government is the sole shareholder in this public entity, so this shareholder has got no intention to privatise this public entity," Mabuza said. "We can be rest assured of that intention and that commitment."